(178, 3, 12, 8, '0', 0, 0, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>LISTENING SECTION</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">In this section of the test, you will have the chance how well you understand spoken English. There are four parts to this section with special directions for each part.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Part I </strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Questions 1 to 4</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Directions: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">ln this part of the test, you will hear some dialogues and questions spoken in English. The questions and the dialogues will be spoken twice. They will not be printed in your test book, so you must listen carefully to understand what the speakers are saying. After you listen to the dialogue and the question about it, read the five possible answers, and decide which one would be the best answer to the question you have heard. Now listen to a sample question.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">You will hear:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Man : I highly appreciate you for helping me choose the right loan I need.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Woman : My pleasure, Sir. I hope you can use the money to buy your dream house.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><sp