(242, 35, 12, 8, '0', 0, 0, '<p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\"><strong>The following text is for questions number 35-38.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Around Bali</strong></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Bali, the fabled &ldquo;island of the Gods&rdquo; has been enchanting visitors for centuries with its rich cultural traditions and spectacular panoramas. As for recreation, there is no shortage of options. Nature walks, horseback riding, diving, surfing-even bungy jumping and white water rafting &ndash; await the adventurers here.</span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Bali Barat National Park</strong></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"margin-left:29px; text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Bali&rsquo;s largest nature reserve encompasses 70.000 hectares of rainforest and 7,000 hectares of coral reefs and is home to many rare species of fauna.</span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Bedugul</strong></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"margin-left:29px; text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">The cool highland resort of Bedugul on the shores of lake Bratan has become a popular retreat for tourists and residents as well.</span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Besakih</strong></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"margin-left:29px; text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Bali&rsquo;s &ldquo;Mother Temple&rdquo; is a sprawling complex of shrines and pavilions set high on the slopes of sacred Mt. Agung.</span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Kuta</strong></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"margin-left:29px; text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Kuta Bay, with its long stretch of white sand and brilliant sunset, has attracted swarms of visitors since its rediscovery by surfers and sun worshippers in the 1970s.</span></p>  <p style=\"margin-left:29px; text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>  <p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\"><em>Taken from: bestworldtourism.com</em></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">According to the text, where is the nice place to stay?</span></p> ', 'Kuta', 'Bekasih', 'Bedugul', 'Island of God', 'Bali Barat National Park', 'sedang', 'c', '2', '2019-09-16 07:26:00', '2019-09-16 07:26:00'),
