(249, 42, 12, 8, '0', 0, 0, '<p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>The following text is for questions number 42-45.</strong></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">Munirwan, a farmer and village head in Meunasah Rayeuk village, North Aceh regency, has been arrested for producing and selling a rice seed variety called IF8 that has not been officially released to the public by the government.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">Munirwan was arrested on July 23. He is facing charges under Article 12 of Law No. 12/1992 on plant cultivation that rules that plant varieties from abroad must be officially released by the government before being permitted to be commercially distributed by farmers.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">The Indonesian Farmer Alliance (API) has condemned the arrest, saying the village head had the good intention to improve the welfare of the villagers.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\">&ldquo;<span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size