(253, 46, 12, 8, '0', 0, 0, '<p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\"><strong>The following text is for questions number 46-47.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>How to Make Chicken Soup</strong></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Ingredients</strong></span></span></span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">350 grams of chicken </span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">2 carrots</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">2 potatoes</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">5 stalks of celeries</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">1 red tomato</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">1 cup of water</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">2 spoons of cooking oil for saut&eacute;ing</span></span></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Spices</strong></span></span></span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">5 onions</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">2 garlic</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">3 candlenuts</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">&frac12; teaspoon of pepper</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">&frac12; tablespoon of salt</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">&frac12; teaspoon of sugar</span></span></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><strong>Procedures</strong></span></span></span></p>  <ul>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Combine the chicken and water. Clean the chicken then dry it.</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Turn on the stove and stir-fry the spices with cooking oil.</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Add water and wait until it boils, then add the chicken.</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Peel the carrots and potatoes. Chop into a few chunks.</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Add the vegetables to the soup. Wait for roughly 30 minutes then add tomatoes and celeries.</span></span></span></p>  </li>  <li>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\">Turn off the stove and chicken soup is ready to serve.</span></span></span></p>  </li> </ul>  <p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>  <p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\"><em>Modified from: maudisini.com</em></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>  <p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:medium\"><span style=\"color:#0c0c0c\"><span style=\"font-family:Garamond,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">What is the function of the text